info.headline: Wind Advisory issued March 05 at 1:30AM PST until March 05 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...West winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 50 mph possible this morning as a compact low brings a brief surge of west wind to the Humboldt County coast and mountain ridges. * WHERE...Humboldt County. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
